WEBVTT

00:00:00.480 --> 00:00:05.278
Hey, good morning family. Praise the Lord. Thank you for joining us today.

00:00:05.279 --> 00:00:10.265
Well, it's Diana and Brandon again, and we have some things on our heart to talk to you about.

00:00:10.266 --> 00:00:20.905
I've been trying to make these videos every day, praying with you and seeking the face of the Lord so that we could be this prayer army that God's called us all to be.

00:00:20.906 --> 00:00:30.883
But there's a lot of people that don't know who we are, where we've come from, and our past, including some of the struggles and successes we've been through.

00:00:30.884 --> 00:00:38.459
Diana and I have been married for quite a while now, going on twenty-some years.

00:00:38.460 --> 00:00:54.185
We set out to be in ministry; it seems like my whole life since I was my son's age, I've always wanted to seek the ministry and have some part of it, even if it was behind the scenes.

00:00:54.186 --> 00:01:05.035
I started traveling and going to Benny Hinn crusades because I saw what he did on TV, and I was like, 'Man, there is something about this.

00:01:05.036 --> 00:01:10.722
Is this fake? Is this real?'I was just curious as a young kid.

00:01:10.723 --> 00:01:19.548
So, I saved up my money as I worked, put it aside, and would go to crusades.

00:01:19.549 --> 00:01:26.544
My dad, or friends and I, would get in the car and drive long distances.

00:01:26.545 --> 00:01:30.981
I flew to Fort Lauderdale and went to Arkansas and Fort Worth.

00:01:30.982 --> 00:01:43.582
There were a lot of places we went to just to experience the glory because we were hungry. I experienced the glory of the Lord there.

00:01:43.583 --> 00:01:55.112
I know he gets a lot of hate now—a lot of people do not like him—and I'm not here to defend him, as I don't know him personally. I just know that I experienced the glory when I was there.

00:01:55.113 --> 00:02:02.736
So, if I bring up a person's name, don't throw eggs at me and say, 'Well, you're saying his name; he's of the devil,'and all that.

00:02:02.737 --> 00:02:06.632
I don't believe they're of the devil, or I wouldn't have gone.

00:02:06.633 --> 00:02:23.919
I only went because I knew in my heart I had a pulling to go and experience the glory, the same way I want to experience it with Billy Burke. I don't chase people; I chase the glory and the anointing.

00:02:23.920 --> 00:02:38.083
When we got married, I told her, 'Let's go to some crusades.'We traveled around and experienced them on our vacations from our ministry jobs.

00:02:38.084 --> 00:02:53.354
I just wanted to be where Jesus was. In the back, I was helping because I was a stocky guy—pretty tall and hefty—so I could catch people.

00:02:53.355 --> 00:03:08.248
A guy named Sam saw me and I told him, 'I'm here to volunteer; I want to usher.'He said, 'Well, you can help the people down off the stage.'I wanted to get as close to the platform as I could so I could see.

00:03:08.249 --> 00:03:17.816
There were times when they wanted me to catch because there were so many people.

00:03:17.817 --> 00:03:27.272
When Benny Hinn took his hand like this, the glory of the Lord knocked me back. I couldn't get up off the ground, and I was hooked.

00:03:27.273 --> 00:03:38.336
I called Diana on the phone and said, 'Hey, you'll never believe what just happened. I just got knocked off my feet.

00:03:38.337 --> 00:03:55.125
It was amazing.'After the service, I went to the back where a man was eating strawberry cake and strawberries. I'll never forget it.

00:03:55.126 --> 00:04:09.492
He said, 'Young man, you're the reason I showed up today.'I looked at him like, 'Who is this old guy?'He said, 'The Lord told me I was supposed to meet you.

00:04:09.493 --> 00:04:15.692
I have a word for you.'He said, 'I'm going to meet twelve of you in the next couple of months.

00:04:15.693 --> 00:04:36.573
You're end-time people that will bring healing to the nations.'He told me I had a mantle on my life like Kathryn Kuhlman, Oral Roberts, and Benny Hinn. He said, 'I'm supposed to pray for you.

00:04:36.574 --> 00:04:54.858
My name is Ralph Wilkerson, and I have Melodyland Christian Center.'I didn't know who that was at the time, but I later learned he had a mega-church in Anaheim.

00:04:54.859 --> 00:05:17.359
He said, 'I'm supposed to lay hands on you and impart a double portion of the anointing on my life onto you by what the Spirit of the Lord has told me to do.'He laid his hands on mine, and suddenly, the fire of the Holy Spirit went through him into me.

00:05:17.360 --> 00:05:31.990
The palms of my hands felt like I had two hot coals in them. He prayed and prophesied over my future, imparting the glory into me.

00:05:31.991 --> 00:05:46.099
I was shook; the power of God was all over me. I was forever changed and have never been the same since that impartation.

00:05:46.100 --> 00:05:59.046
At the time, I was working at a grocery store, sacked groceries for years because I had a lot of learning problems.

00:05:59.047 --> 00:06:20.901
I did that until a lady named Debbie called and said, 'Brandon, we have a job for you at the ministry if you want to be a janitor here.'I told her, 'I'm not interested. I'm called to preach and prophesy.

00:06:20.902 --> 00:06:39.500
I am not a janitor.'She said, 'Well, I think you're making a mistake, but if that's your choice, okay.'After I hung up, the Holy Spirit said, 'You take that job and you take it now,'rebuking me for my attitude.

00:06:39.501 --> 00:06:46.318
I called her back and said, 'Debbie, I feel the Lord has told me to take this job.

00:06:46.319 --> 00:07:10.245
My flesh doesn't want to, but I'll do it.'It was during a 30-day revival called '30 Days of Glory.'I started cleaning and helping out, and after the meeting, they hired me full-time.

00:07:10.246 --> 00:07:22.497
Not knowing what God was doing, I started cleaning in the back.

00:07:22.498 --> 00:07:32.913
They had prayer school every Thursday where they taught people to pray, just like I do with you now.

00:07:32.914 --> 00:07:40.660
On my breaks, I would sit in the back and listen to a lady named Gina and Pastor Terri.

00:07:40.661 --> 00:07:53.502
They would pray every Thursday, along with a lady named Annie. I listened to them all the time while I was cleaning.

00:07:53.503 --> 00:07:57.245
On Mondays they had healing school, and on Thursdays they had prayer.

00:07:57.246 --> 00:08:05.131
I would listen as they ministered to the sick. This went on for three years.

00:08:05.132 --> 00:08:07.408
I started taking care of the ministry plans, the ministry, and the balconies.

00:08:07.409 --> 00:08:14.650
I started going down to the main house of this preacher. I took care of things.

00:08:14.651 --> 00:08:19.288
I took care of their cars, I cleaned things, I did a lot; I cleaned carpets.

00:08:19.289 --> 00:08:29.716
So I started getting to go and help out and get things ready for main guest speakers that were coming, like Oral Roberts and a lot of others.

00:08:29.717 --> 00:08:42.088
That's what I did. As I kept growing there, I started to have more favor, and I would just keep going because the Lord just had His hand on me.

00:08:42.089 --> 00:08:50.491
Well, I learned to pray. They had a guest speaker come to an all-staff meeting; his name was Reinhard Bonnke.

00:08:50.492 --> 00:09:07.244
I don't know if very many of you know who Reinhard Bonnke is, but Reinhard Bonnke was there, and he was telling the people thank you because this main ministry supported a lot of his crusades throughout Africa, and he wanted to say thank you for giving him money to help bring in the lost for Jesus.

00:09:07.245 --> 00:09:14.008
He was praying there, and all of a sudden, he said, 'I feel led to pray for the staff. I feel led to pray for the staff.

00:09:14.009 --> 00:09:21.583
So staff, if you feel you want to get prayed for, come down to the front, and I'll lay hands on you.'And I think probably everybody went down there.

00:09:21.584 --> 00:09:27.394
I ran down there because I was like, 'This guy's talking about raising the dead. He's talking about seeing people get healed.

00:09:27.395 --> 00:09:54.073
He's talking about millions of people getting saved.'And I was like, 'I want a part of this.'So when he came down to the front, he put his hands on top of my head, and he stopped and said, 'I put a double portion of the anointing on my life onto you.'I kid you not, it felt like a bolt of lightning hit me that day and knocked me on my backside again, and in that, I had impartation.

00:09:54.074 --> 00:10:08.877
I got up, and I was forever—I'm telling you, that was one, besides Ralph Wilkerson, that was a forever-changing experience when Reinhard touched me.

00:10:08.878 --> 00:10:25.038
I'm telling you all, I still have that fire of the Holy Ghost stirring on the inside of me, and it's something I—you know, as a kid, you wanted to be bad or whatever, you wanted to go out and hang with your friends.

00:10:25.039 --> 00:10:35.879
But I always had the Holy Ghost always stirring me. I couldn't sin without having that in the back of my mind: 'I've got a call in my life.

00:10:35.880 --> 00:10:45.260
I have impartation.'It was always something convicting me; I don't know how else to describe it.

00:10:45.261 --> 00:10:51.833
It was just heavy on me, the Holy Spirit telling me, 'Don't do this. You've got a call.

00:10:51.834 --> 00:10:57.596
You've got to do this.'And then I started having dreams and visions when I started praying.

00:10:57.597 --> 00:11:02.033
I was in the back one day at that church and the Lord spoke to me.

00:11:02.034 --> 00:11:13.253
He said, 'I'm putting a mantle of prayer from this sister that went home.'And if I said her name, everybody would know who she was. But the Lord said, 'I'm going to give you that mantle.

00:11:13.254 --> 00:11:29.973
And as this comes on you, you will pray and it will be different, and you're going to start to see.'So I started looking up on the internet who this woman was and I started trying to find books and teachings about who she was that the Lord told me about.

00:11:29.974 --> 00:11:39.356
And I was like, 'Okay, Lord.'So I started studying her. And the more I prayed in the back with Gina and them, it just kept bubbling up on me.

00:11:39.357 --> 00:11:45.100
And I started seeing things. I started seeing terrorist attacks; I started seeing all kinds of things.

00:11:45.101 --> 00:11:54.293
I'm talking about when 9/11 happened as a young man. I saw all that; I had it all down to everything that was going on.

00:11:54.294 --> 00:12:07.078
The Lord showed me and I had specific details of things, and people were like, 'Well, who is this kid?'because I was just a young kid. I just started seeing the spirit that way.

00:12:07.079 --> 00:12:15.846
And then the more I prayed, the more I sought Him, the more I started seeing angels, the more I started talking, and I had a visitation from Jesus.

00:12:15.847 --> 00:12:26.389
I've had so many visions and impartations of seeing into the spirit realm that I can't count them all anymore; you lose track.

00:12:26.390 --> 00:12:34.071
And I don't say that all to brag; I tell you this because I'm trying to tell you who we are.

00:12:34.072 --> 00:12:46.595
And that's what's happened. When the Lord told me to leave Fort Worth and leave that ministry, we came here.

00:12:46.596 --> 00:12:54.513
I thought for sure at that time, because of the way I prayed and things were going on with me, that I was going to step right into ministry at a young age.

00:12:54.514 --> 00:13:09.777
And the Lord called me to be a janitor again. I cleaned toilets at that mega-church, learning how a mega-church functions so I could run it with my eyes closed.

00:13:09.778 --> 00:13:17.034
I'm just being real. I watched everything and I learned everything I could from the staff to the music, to all of it, how it flowed.

00:13:17.034 --> 00:13:24.733
I was there every Sunday and every Wednesday. That was my job. I opened it, I closed it, and I set the alarm.

00:13:24.734 --> 00:13:29.073
I was everything; I walked around and cleaned the bathrooms and got everything done.

00:13:29.074 --> 00:13:39.245
And that was what I did for 13 years—10 years on staff like that and then the other time I was doing the floors in other campuses.

00:13:39.246 --> 00:13:45.992
So altogether 13-some years, and it was the longest 13 years of my life.

00:13:45.993 --> 00:13:51.701
So Diana's going to tell her side, what she's done, and I'll let her talk a little bit.

00:13:51.702 --> 00:14:01.053
Yeah. So I worked at the ministry too. I did the prisoner letters and counted the offerings and that kind of thing.

00:14:01.054 --> 00:14:09.216
And then we met at a Bible study—at Jeremy's Bible study. Yeah.

00:14:09.217 --> 00:14:20.536
And then when we moved here, I worked at the grandson of the main minister's. We met at a Bible study and we've talked ever since.

00:14:20.537 --> 00:14:28.258
And then when we moved here, when we worked at the other ministry, I counted offerings there as well.

00:14:28.259 --> 00:14:35.705
And after Megan got diagnosed with autism, she was still in diapers. It was really, really severe.

00:14:35.706 --> 00:14:41.789
Brendan's told the story; it was a really, really dark time in our life.

00:14:41.790 --> 00:14:45.819
We're still going through that, but we're seeing progress.

00:14:45.820 --> 00:14:51.559
And so that's good, ever since she got prayed over by Billy Burke.

00:14:51.560 --> 00:15:08.442
So, but whenever she was diagnosed at the ministry that we were at, they were telling me that I couldn't work from home and that if I went and got my degree, I might get a promotion, but we would have to pay for it ourselves.

00:15:08.443 --> 00:15:15.088
So I was really praying about it because I really needed to be home with Megan a lot and it was just a lot.

00:15:15.089 --> 00:15:21.837
They said you could be at home working part-time and be there for a season because of how bad Megan was, right?

00:15:21.838 --> 00:15:26.717
But they said one day you're going to have to come back up here. They told me I was going to have to go back up there.

00:15:26.718 --> 00:15:36.156
So we were really praying about it and felt that the Lord was leading me to go to ORU.

00:15:36.157 --> 00:15:44.472
They had this program where you could go online, and it was something that I was interested in.

00:15:44.473 --> 00:16:01.632
So I started doing that, and I would work all day at the ministry and then come home and write papers and essays and all the stuff at ORU, do all my tests, watch everything, and I worked on that until sometimes 2:00 in the morning.

00:16:01.633 --> 00:16:09.525
And so I did that for four years for my bachelor's. Yeah, four years there at ORU.

00:16:09.526 --> 00:16:17.750
And don't be modest, she made a 4.0 all the way through college with her bachelor's, by the grace of God.

00:16:17.751 --> 00:16:26.419
Yes, a 4.0 by the grace of God. Summa Cum Laude, graduated top of the class for business and for accounting.

00:16:26.420 --> 00:16:33.462
Yeah, got that. Then, because you specialized in business and everything, right?

00:16:33.463 --> 00:16:39.994
And then after those four years, then she said, 'Brandon, I feel like I'm supposed to keep going.'I said, 'Are you kidding?

00:16:39.995 --> 00:16:49.696
We just did four years, every night of our life for four years.'I haven't really got to talk to you because I was taking care of Megan and Braden.

00:16:49.697 --> 00:17:00.661
I told her, "I'm exhausted with this, but if you feel led to go, honey, I'll support you."She said, "Well, it takes three years for my master's, Brandon."Yeah, to do another three years.

00:17:00.662 --> 00:17:08.819
I thought, "Dear God,"because I was thinking it would probably be more beneficial pay-wise.

00:17:08.820 --> 00:17:26.805
So I got my major and then my master's in accounting and taxation.

00:17:26.806 --> 00:17:33.678
She made a 4.0 all the way through that. You cannot skip that part, baby. You worked hard.

00:17:33.679 --> 00:17:42.383
She made straight A's through her master's, got an accounting degree, and was able to specialize in taxation, right?

00:17:42.384 --> 00:17:53.716
Taxes and doing CPA stuff for ministries. She wanted to do the ministry finances at the church we were working for.

00:17:53.717 --> 00:17:59.633
That was the goal, to be the head of it because it made good money there.

00:17:59.634 --> 00:18:07.471
I was just trying to provide for Megan's needs, and that gets really expensive when you're a parent.

00:18:07.472 --> 00:18:22.397
All her therapists were saying, "You've got to prepare for her future and she needs a savings account."So I was thinking we have to keep going.

00:18:22.398 --> 00:18:29.630
Maybe that'll help make more money if I get my master's, so that's why I just kept going.

00:18:29.631 --> 00:18:45.480
There were so many nights that I would literally crawl into bed crying, and I would say I didn't even understand what I was doing in some classes.

00:18:45.481 --> 00:18:50.798
It was pretty intense. There were classes like that—what I'm talking about.

00:18:50.799 --> 00:19:00.767
She would have a problem in some of those master's classes that would take up two or three pages, and she'd keep flipping it over and say, "I got it right."I remember you crying.

00:19:00.768 --> 00:19:09.312
I prayed for you. I cried and cried. There were several classes where I don't know how I did it other than the grace of God.

00:19:09.313 --> 00:19:15.818
I remember I would just sit there and cry out to God in the shower and say, "Lord, you told me to do this.

00:19:15.819 --> 00:19:27.969
I need some help here because I don't know what I'm doing in this class."Then I would pray, take a break, go back to the class, and see it in a different light.

00:19:27.970 --> 00:19:34.168
That's how I made it. Sometimes in the homework I would fail, but I'd make the A.

00:19:34.169 --> 00:19:42.263
Holy Spirit would help bring things to my remembrance and help my memory during the tests to score higher.

00:19:42.264 --> 00:19:51.218
I don't know how she did it other than the grace of God because she didn't have a tutor.

00:19:51.219 --> 00:19:58.246
She watched YouTube videos of someone teaching because the teachers were not very helpful.

00:19:58.247 --> 00:20:06.954
She watched it online, did the course, and did the assignments, and that's all she had.

00:20:06.955 --> 00:20:14.232
Sometimes I told her, "I don't know how you're going to do this,"but I was going to pray in the Holy Ghost.

00:20:14.233 --> 00:20:26.723
What really helped was that in high school, I had some really good teachers who taught me how to write essays.

00:20:26.724 --> 00:20:45.562
I was pretty decent at writing essays going into college. We wrote so many essays for professors, and I got really good at it.

00:20:45.563 --> 00:20:55.400
The reason I bring up her testimony is that she did all that with two babies.

00:20:55.401 --> 00:21:03.672
One had special needs so severe that we couldn't sleep, functioning off no sleep and staying up.

00:21:03.673 --> 00:21:13.459
We did all this for seven years, pushing forward. Now we have a ton of student loans, but we'll get it taken care of.

00:21:13.460 --> 00:21:24.114
It is a major amount of student loans. Then, when our pastor fell morally, she had just graduated.

00:21:24.115 --> 00:21:31.038
We were thinking we'd announce she has her degree. I'm so proud of her.

00:21:31.039 --> 00:21:40.762
I said, "Baby, you're like Rocky! You did it! You knocked down the big Russian guy."I told her, "We can do this now.

00:21:40.763 --> 00:21:46.710
We're going to make decent money."We were living on food stamps and barely making it the whole time.

00:21:46.711 --> 00:22:00.742
I told her, "Thank God we're there. Maybe we'll make six figures and be able to pay back these student loans."We were so excited.

00:22:00.743 --> 00:22:13.261
The next two weeks, she went in and they said, "We have an announcement to make."The pastor we were working for, who told her she could run the finances, fell morally.

00:22:13.262 --> 00:22:30.624
I got laid off. She kept doing the accounting and the offerings, but I told her we had to get out of there because they weren't going to promote her.

00:22:30.625 --> 00:22:45.773
They said they couldn't anymore because they laid off so many people; their finances tanked.

00:22:45.774 --> 00:22:54.373
That happened the year I graduated. God had other plans, which was to do eBay.

00:22:54.374 --> 00:23:00.658
That all came through her too, because of learning the business side of things.

00:23:00.659 --> 00:23:07.776
People ask, "How did you learn to hear God the way you hear Him?"Well, I had always seen things since I was a teen.

00:23:07.777 --> 00:23:16.772
I pray and the Lord shows me things, but I started developing the prophetic ear of really hearing the voice of the Lord.

00:23:16.773 --> 00:23:31.735
Don't crucify me, but this is just real. Don't get mad when I tell you how I heard. It was always watching sports with the Lord.

00:23:31.736 --> 00:23:39.192
That may sound crazy, but I would sit on the couch and we would talk about the score of the game.

00:23:39.193 --> 00:23:45.997
I would pray in the spirit, and the Lord said, "Brandon, I'm going to teach you to hear because you love sports.

00:23:45.998 --> 00:24:01.957
You love basketball, football, and baseball, and I'm going to talk to you so you can practice my presence through this."He would say, "This is who's going to win and in what quarter."He would tell me each thing step by step.

00:24:01.957 --> 00:24:11.352
He would tell me in advance who was going to win the World Series and the Super Bowl. I would write it down and tell Diana privately.

00:24:11.353 --> 00:24:21.839
The Lord said this team would win and who would be in the Super Bowl at the end of the year, including the score.

00:24:21.840 --> 00:24:28.893
Every single time, it was right. Then he started talking to me about the weather.

00:24:28.894 --> 00:24:36.763
He would say, "On this day, it's going to rain. This day, a cold front's coming through.

00:24:36.764 --> 00:24:47.865
In four weeks, this is what's going to happen."He would tell me how much rain we'd get.

00:24:47.866 --> 00:24:52.957
It was always something, but I think my favorite thing was always the weather.

00:24:52.957 --> 00:24:56.715
I loved it. He still talks to me about the weather, but not like that.

00:24:56.716 --> 00:24:59.182
Now we talk about everything because it's like we're on here.

00:24:59.183 --> 00:25:12.691
But I loved the simplicity of the relationship back then, how I practiced His presence and we would talk about sports. My main thing was the NBA Thunder.

00:25:12.692 --> 00:25:24.552
I would always tell him, and so much so, March Madness came and I would pick the teams that were going to win for March Madness college basketball.

00:25:24.553 --> 00:25:35.345
But the Lord told me, 'If you ever bet or gamble off of what I'm telling you, I'll never speak to you this way again. This is something private between me and you.

00:25:35.346 --> 00:25:44.994
You can learn this because you can learn and practice my presence and hear my voice.'Brandon, this was something that you did not talk about at the time.

00:25:44.995 --> 00:25:51.404
I never told anybody; I was always private about it, and it was something that Diana and I knew, and my son.

00:25:51.405 --> 00:25:59.158
It was always fun to us. We always knew when the weather was coming because God always talked about it.

00:25:59.159 --> 00:26:05.213
I would hear in April how the weather was going to be all through the summer.

00:26:05.214 --> 00:26:09.685
It was really cool, I'm telling you. I would write things down.

00:26:09.686 --> 00:26:16.558
I literally told her, 'By this time, this is how the summer will be,'and I'd tell her the temperatures.

00:26:16.559 --> 00:26:28.797
The Lord would tell me how many hurricanes would be in the summer, how many major hurricanes would hit America, and how many major tornadoes would come. He would always tell me far in advance.

00:26:28.798 --> 00:26:43.099
I would know exactly how many hurricanes and the category and where they would hit precisely at the location when they would forecast a week in advance.

00:26:43.100 --> 00:26:57.632
I'd see it develop in the Gulf of Mexico or out in the Caribbean, and He would say, 'This is where that hurricane's going to hit, and it's going to hit this town.'He would tell me, and I would tell people—I would try to hint around to them.

00:26:57.633 --> 00:27:07.064
I would say, 'Hey, this is where I believe it's going to hit. They're all saying it's going to hit here, but...'And then whenever Katrina happened, I knew.

00:27:07.065 --> 00:27:13.918
There are just things that the Lord talks to you about, and I'm just being real.

00:27:13.919 --> 00:27:19.355
This is how I learned. So Diana and I just kept practicing His presence.

00:27:19.356 --> 00:27:26.114
The more that happened, the more I got confident in hearing Him, and the more He started talking to me and developing other things.

00:27:26.115 --> 00:27:35.867
Then He wanted us to eBay. To make a long story short, we started doing that and He started telling me where to go to get stuff out of thrift stores.

00:27:35.868 --> 00:27:46.383
We started doing eBay because we had a bill that was due and we didn't have the money to pay it because he had just gotten laid off.

00:27:46.384 --> 00:27:50.729
We were trying to come up with a way to not have to borrow the money.

